===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*m-tshyar ~ *g-zyar||thorn, nail, tack}} (provisional) (STEDT); cognate with {{cog|bo|ཚེར་མ|t=thorn, thorn bush}}, {{m|bo|གཟེར་བ|t=to bore into}}, and {{m|bo|གཟེར|t=nail}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

{{och-l|刺|tr=*tsekh}} "attack, satirize" ({{w|Zuozhuan}}) < "criticize" ({{w|Shijing}}) < lit. "cause to be stabbed" is exopassive/exoactive derivation of {{och-l|刺|tr=*tsek}} "pierce, stab" (ibid.); {{och-l|朿|tr=tsʰie<sup>C</sup>}} "thorn" ({{w|Shuowen jiezi|SW}}) is Han period's general tone-C derivation of {{och-l|刺|tr=*tsʰiek}} (ibid.)

